1.  Beginning with Version 1.50 of the data specs, this field is no longer active and is now blank filler.  Agencies may continue to use this field if they wish, but the contents of this field will be ignored by the State System.

*1.  For the original submission of a record use 00 (zero, zero) as the value.  If correction records are submitted, increment this count with each correction: 01, 02, 03.*2.  A record will be rejected based upon CORRECTION_NUM if EITHER of the following two conditions apply:   a.  If there are NO MATCHING RECORDS on the state database and CORRECTION_NUM is not equal to 00; or   b.  If there are ONE OR MORE MATCHING RECORDS on the state database, and CORRECTION_NUM is not one integer greater than the greatest CORRECTION_NUM among the matching state database records."Matching records" are defined as records which meet ALL FOUR of the following conditions:   -identical agency (HHA_AGENCY_ID);   -identical reason for assessment (M0100_ASSMT_REASON);   -identical effective date (M0030_START_CARE_DT for a start of care record, M0032_ROC_DT for a resumption of care record, M0090_INFO_COMPLETED_DT for a recertification or other follow-up record, and M0906_DC_TRAN_DTH_DT for a transfer to inpatient facility, death at home, or discharge record);   -the resident is identified as the same resident on the basis of name (M0040_PAT_LNAME and M0040_PAT_FNAME), gender (M0069_PAT_GENDER), birthdate (M0066_PAT_BIRTH_DT), and Social Security Number (M0064_SSN).

1.  If the HHA has a CMS Certification number, it must be entered in this field.  Otherwise enter spaces.*2.  M0010_CCN must match FED_ID on the header record.

*1.  If a standard branch ID (i.e., not N or P) is submitted, then M0014_BRANCH_STATE cannot be blank.2.  M0014_BRANCH_STATE should contain the state code for the State where the agency branch office is located.

*1.  The following rules apply to M0016_BRANCH_ID:   a.  If the assessment was performed by an HHA which has no branches or by a subunit which has no branches, then M0016_BRANCH_ID  must contain the following: "N         " (N followed by 9 spaces).  This indicates that the assessment was completed by an HHA or subunit which has no branches.     b.  If the assessment was performed by the home office of an HHA which has branches or by the home office of a subunit which has branches, then M0016_BRANCH_ID must contain the following: "P         " (P  followed by 9 spaces).  This indicates that the assessment was completed by the home office (an HHA parent or subunit -- not a branch).   c.  If the assessment was performed by a branch, then M0016_BRANCH_ID  must contain a standard branch ID.  It must contain numbers or uppercase letters in bytes 1 and 2, Q in byte 3, numbers or uppercase letters in bytes 4 through 7, and numbers in bytes 8 through 10.   d.  If M0016_BRANCH_ID  does not contain a standard branch ID, "N         ", or "P         ", a fatal error will result and the record will be rejected.   e.  If a standard branch ID (i.e., not N or P) is submitted, then it will be checked against the system table of the HHA’s or subunit’s current and past branch IDs.  If the submitted branch ID does not match the list of current IDs but does match a past branch ID, then a warning will be issued and the assessment record will be accepted.  If the submitted branch ID does not match a current or past branch ID, then the assessment record will be rejected (i.e., it will result in a fatal error).  f.  If a standard branch ID (i.e., not N or P) is submitted, then M0014_BRANCH_STATE cannot be blank.

It must be alphanumeric with no embedded dashes or spaces.   b.  If the first character is numeric (0 through 9), then the first 9 characters must be numeric.   c. It must not equal any of the following values: 111111111, 333333333, 999999999, 123456789.

*1.  If this field is not filled with dashes, it must be less than the current date (see consistency note #4, below).*2.  If this field is not filled with dashes, it must be no more than 140 years prior to the current date.*3.  If this field is not filled with dashes, it must be earlier than or equal to each of the following dates (if the date listed below is not blank on the assessment):  -M0030_START_CARE_DT  -M0032_ROC_DATE  -M0090_INFO_COMPLETED_DT  -M0903_LAST_HOME_VISIT  -M0906_DC_TRAN_DTH_DT  -M1005_INP_DISCHARGE_DT*4.  Assessments must not be submitted to the State if the patient was less than 18 years of age at the time the assessment was completed (as determined by comparing M0066_PAT_BIRTH_DT with M0090_INFO_COMPLETED_DT).  Age should be tested in the following way:   a.  If  M0066_PAT_BIRTH_DT is completely filled with dashes, age cannot be computed and this consistency check does not apply.   b.  If the month in M0066_PAT_BIRTH_DT is filled with spaces, replace the month with "12" for the purpose of calculating age.   c.  If the day in M0066_PAT_BIRTH_DT is filled with spaces, replace the day with the last day of the month for the purpose of calculating age.   d.  Provisionally compute age (in years) by subtracting the year in M0066_PAT_BIRTH_DT from the year in M0090_INFO_COMPLETED_DT.   e.  If the month in M0090_INFO_COMPLETED_DT is less than  the month in M0066_PAT_BIRTH_DT, then subtract 1 from the provisional age computed in (d) above.   f.  If the month in M0090_INFO_COMPLETED_DT is equal to the month in M0066_PAT_BIRTH_DT and if the day in M0090_INFO_COMPLETED_DT is less than the day in M0066_PAT_BIRTH_DT, then subtract 1 from the provisional age computed in (d) above.   g.  If the age, as calculated above, is less than 18, the assessment must not be submitted (I.e., it will be rejected).

FIELD_DESCRIPTION: (M1010) Inpatient Stay Within Last 14 Days: ICD Code 1
CONSISTENCY: *1.  If M1000_DC_NONE_14_DA = 1, then M1005_INP_DISCHARGE_DT through M1012_INP_UK_ICD must be skipped (blank).*2.  If M1000_DC_NONE_14_DA = 0 then the following rule applies:    a).  If any item M1000_DC_LTC_14_DA  through M1000_DC_OTH_14_DA is equal to 1, then M1010_14_DAY_INP1_ICD cannot be blank.3.  If state law prohibits transmission of certain ICD9 codes (e.g., HIV or STD diagnoses), these codes will be blanked out by the state system if found on records submitted by HHAs within that state.  If any item from M1010_14_DAY_INP1_ICD through M1010_14_DAY_INP6_ICD contains such a code on a submitted record, it will be blanked out.  If any of these items is blanked out, but a valid code remains in a subsequent M1010 item,  the non-blank codes will be "moved up" so that no blank items remain before consistency note #2 is tested.  Therefore, if a non-blank value is required in M1010_14_DAY_INP1_ICD on a particular record, and all of the M1010 items contain blank and/or prohibited codes, a fatal error will result and the record will be rejected.  As long as at least one M1010 item contains a non-blank, allowable code, a fatal error will not occur.*4.  Note that E-codes and V-codes are not allowed in this field; the first character of this field must be blank.

FIELD_DESCRIPTION: (M0010) Inpatient Stay Within Last 14 Days: ICD Code 2
CONSISTENCY: *1.  If M1000_DC_NONE_14_DA = 1, then M1005_INP_DISCHARGE_DT through M1012_INP_UK_ICD must be skipped (blank).*2.  If M1000_DC_NONE_14_DA = 0 then the following rules apply:    a). FIELD_DESCRIPTION: (M1016) Regimen Change In Past 14 Days: ICD Code 5
CONSISTENCY: *1.  If M1016_CHGREG_ICD_NA=0, then at least one item from M1016_CHGREG_ICD1 through M1016_CHGREG_ICD6 must be non-blank (i.e., must contain an ICD9 code).  Note that this edit is applied after any prohibited codes are blanked out (see consistency note #3).*2.  If M1016_CHGREG_ICD_NA=1, then all items from M1016_CHGREG_ICD1 through M1016_CHGREG_ICD6 must be blank.  Note that this edit is applied after any prohibited codes are blanked out (see consistency note #3).3.  If state law prohibits transmission of certain ICD9 codes (e.g., HIV or STD diagnoses), these codes will be blanked out by the state system if found on records submitted by HHAs within that state.  If any item from M1016_CHGREG_ICD1 through M1016_CHGREG_ICD6 contains such a code on a submitted record, it will be blanked out.  If any of these items is blanked out, but a valid code remains in a subsequent M1016 item,  the non-blank codes will be "moved up" so that no blank items remain.  Consistency notes #1 and #2 will be applied after any prohibited codes are blanked out.
